verbose_text: As presented in XREF_TABLE, supplementation with thyme and rosemary significantly increased plasma calcium levels in both T and R groups (8.92 +/- 0.13 and 8.54 +/- 0.11) compared to the positive control group (7.57 +/- 0.12); on the other hand, magnesium and phosphorus levels had no significant changes among all groups.
